Czech Stocks Jump Most in 3 Months on CME Earnings, U.S. Orders

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-04-27T15:04:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/czech-stocks-jump-most-in-3-months-on-cme-earnings-u-s-orders.html
The Czech Republic’s main equity
index rose the most in almost three months as  Central European
Media Enterprises Ltd. (CETV)  said its first-quarter loss narrowed and
a U.S. report showed durable-goods orders climbed in March.  The PX gauge of 15 companies gained 1.2 percent to 1,263.6
at its 4:28 p.m. close in  Prague , its biggest jump since Feb. 4.  Central European Media jumped 6 percent, the most since
March 3, to 367 koruna.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)  rose 1.6 percent,
the most in a month, to 855 koruna, ending two days of declines.
 CEZ AS (CEZ) , the country’s biggest power utility, added 1.4 percent
to 928 koruna, its highest close in 10 months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
